{"id":14881405,"mediaExerciseId":"0990c097-26db-438e-a88e-c7ffbc6332cb","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612376,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":452,"solutions":[{"id":5994866,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine expected return. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/f5c99c6f65c8a565b77875ad0c8f3449/lateximg_large.png","width":790},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/f5c99c6f65c8a565b77875ad0c8f3449/lateximg.png","width":394}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is the net income or loss that an investor predicts on investments given known interest rates.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/db28ed1035708c9f4fb2fae385f1ea77/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/db28ed1035708c9f4fb2fae385f1ea77/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's first identify the given amounts in the problem: \n\n\n| | Amount$\\hspace{5pt}$| \n|:--|--:| \n|Recession: ||\n|Probability return | 10% | \n|Portfolio return |-15%|\n|Normal:||\n|Probability return| 60%|\n|Portfolio return| 9%|\n|Boom: ||\n|Probability return | 30%| \n|Portfolio return|23%|","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is computed as follows: \n\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&=\\sum_{\\text{}}{\\text{}_{R}} {\\text{PR $\\times$ R}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere: \n\nPR = Probability return \\\nR = Return","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":220,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/819cea969b17ba6caf2d8b7e6971094f/lateximg_large.png","width":702},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/819cea969b17ba6caf2d8b7e6971094f/lateximg.png","width":351}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let us insert the provided data to the formula from step 4. As an illustration, here's what it looks like: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&= {\\text{[10\\% $\\times$ (-15\\%)] + (60\\% $\\times$ 9\\%) + (30\\% $\\times$ 23\\%)}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":174,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/9c45b28c5d205f19e58fb6bfd305079d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":88,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/9c45b28c5d205f19e58fb6bfd305079d/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let us compute the portfolios's expected return. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&= {\\text{[10\\% $\\times$ (-15\\%)] + (60\\% $\\times$ 9\\%) + (30\\% $\\times$ 23\\%)}}\\\\\n&={\\text{(-1.50\\%) + 5.40\\% + 6.90\\% }}\\\\\n&={\\textbf{10.80\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":252,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/623c4abd1ec6c6885e960c87095f0984/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":127,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/8f2e84c9766796c4f9b120ca59bdb423/623c4abd1ec6c6885e960c87095f0984/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**To conclude, the expected return is 10.80%.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"cb3e2932-3735-48e5-babe-ee0a0f49723c","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881406,"exerciseName":"7","page":452,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d555d692-bacf-450d-9c6f-940cf499f031","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-7-d555d692-bacf-450d-9c6f-940cf499f031"},{"id":14881407,"exerciseName":"8","page":452,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ad77af10-3e61-4c35-a60f-318193bc3f90","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-8-ad77af10-3e61-4c35-a60f-318193bc3f90"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881404,"exerciseName":"5","page":452,"hasSolution":true,"med